    <subsection>
        <title>1.1 - What are differential equations?</title>
        <p>
            In this section, we will learn language to describe and classify differential equations. This section satisfies module objectives 1-3.
            <ol>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/zs-1vviWWJY">🎥Video 1.1.1</url> (1:43). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/344568">✅Checkpoint 1.1.1</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/x-mNPZuX33Y">🎥Video 1.1.2</url> (2:02). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/344570">✅Checkpoint 1.1.2</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> 🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Try finding the order of the diffential equations given in problems 1-8 in Exercises 1.1 (pg. 10). </p></li>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/Db-199xwWcw">🎥Video 1.1.3</url> (4:51). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/344572">✅Checkpoint 1.1.3</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> 🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Determine whether each of the diffential equations given in problems 1-8 in Exercises 1.1 (pg. 10) are linear. </p></li>
