    <subsection>
        <title>1.3 - Why should I find solutions to differential equations?</title>
        <p>
            In this section, we will model some simple real-world phenomena using differential equations. We will also investigate the additional context we can glean from using differential equations (as opposed to algebraic equations) in these models. 
            <ol>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/bzhYY0xXufM">🎥Video 1.4.1</url> (7:38). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/344576">✅Checkpoint 1.3.1</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> 🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Problems 1, 3, 5, 9, 13 in Exercises 1.3 (pg. 28). </p></li> 
            </ol>
            After completing this list, you can complete problem 3 from homework 1. 
        </p>
    </subsection>
        
</section>
